SIF LAI comparison

D. Emin

December 19, 2018

Introduction

Descriptive statistics of HyPlant SIF data was shown in another document. The procedure to retrieve LAI and Chl were described in another document. Here we will explore the relationship between canopy structure (LAI, CHL, VI) and SIF (760, 687, ratio, total). Furthermore, we will explore the shape and the strength of these relatioships across scales.

HyPlant occupies an intermediate scale. Used to study the regional variability of SIF. It produces a nominal spatial resolution of 1 m2 - high enough to study the within field variability of SIF

this analysis is based on one agricultural crop - sugar beet, grown on 59 fields.

Nominal scale

SIF vs canopy structure

SIF vs VI

SIF vs VI at the nominal scale

There is a negative relationship between SIF ration (SIF687 / SIF760) and LAI. This is obvious since SIF 687 (the nominator) changes less than SIF760 (denominator) leading to a smaller ratio with bigger LAI.

Visibly the slope changes significantly between mean and median relationship, but thus us due to the proportionaly higher influence of several small values at the left end of the distribution.
Scale dependence of the linear relationship between SIF760 to all others.
